events.description: King Huneric of the Vandals replaces Nicene bishops with Arian ones, and banishes some to Corsica.
events.html: • 484 – King Huneric of the Vandals replaces Nicene bishops with Arian ones, and banishes some to Corsica.[1]

events.description: The English are defeated at the Battle of Roslin, in the First War of Scottish Independence.
events.html: • 1303 – The English are defeated at the Battle of Roslin, in the First War of Scottish Independence.[2]

events.description: King Charles III of Naples and Hungary is assassinated at Buda.
events.html: • 1386 – King Charles III of Naples and Hungary is assassinated at Buda.[3]

events.description: A Spanish-Austrian army defeats a French army at the Battle of Pavia.
events.html: • 1525 – A Spanish-Austrian army defeats a French army at the Battle of Pavia.[4]

events.description: Coronation of Ferdinand I as the king of Bohemia in Prague.
events.html: • 1527 – Coronation of Ferdinand I as the king of Bohemia in Prague.[5]

events.description: Treaty of Nagyvárad between Holy Roman Emperor Ferdinand I and King John Zápolya of Hungary and Croatia.
events.html: • 1538 – Treaty of Nagyvárad between Holy Roman Emperor Ferdinand I and King John Zápolya of Hungary and Croatia.[6]

events.description: With the papal bull Inter gravissimas, Pope Gregory XIII announces the Gregorian calendar.
events.html: • 1582 – With the papal bull Inter gravissimas, Pope Gregory XIII announces the Gregorian calendar.[7]

events.description: The last battle of the Cudgel War takes place on the Santavuori Hill in Ilmajoki, Ostrobothnia.
events.html: • 1597 – The last battle of the Cudgel War takes place on the Santavuori Hill in Ilmajoki, Ostrobothnia.[8]

events.description: L'Orfeo by Claudio Monteverdi, one of the first works recognized as an opera, receives its première performance.
events.html: • 1607 – L'Orfeo by Claudio Monteverdi, one of the first works recognized as an opera, receives its première performance.[9]

events.description: Rinaldo by George Frideric Handel, the first Italian opera written for the London stage, is premièred.
events.html: • 1711 – Rinaldo by George Frideric Handel, the first Italian opera written for the London stage, is premièred.[10]

events.description: Battle of Karnal: The army of Iranian ruler Nader Shah defeats the forces of the Mughal emperor of India, Muhammad Shah.
events.html: • 1739 – Battle of Karnal: The army of Iranian ruler Nader Shah defeats the forces of the Mughal emperor of India, Muhammad Shah.[11]

events.description: In Marbury v. Madison, the Supreme Court of the United States establishes the principle of judicial review.
events.html: • 1803 – In Marbury v. Madison, the Supreme Court of the United States establishes the principle of judicial review.[12]

entities.name: Supreme Court of the United States

events.description: London's Drury Lane Theatre burns to the ground, leaving its owner, Irish writer and politician Richard Brinsley Sheridan, destitute.
events.html: • 1809 – London's Drury Lane Theatre burns to the ground, leaving its owner, Irish writer and politician Richard Brinsley Sheridan, destitute.[13]

events.description: Britain invades and captures the French colony of Martinique
events.html: • 1809 – Britain invades and captures the French colony of Martinique[14]

entities.name: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

events.description: Treaty of Paris between Napoleon and Frederick William III of Prussia against Russia is signed
events.html: • 1812 – Treaty of Paris between Napoleon and Frederick William III of Prussia against Russia is signed[15]

events.description: Sinking of HMS Peacock by USS Hornet on the Demerara River, Guyana
events.html: • 1813 – Sinking of HMS Peacock by USS Hornet on the Demerara River, Guyana[16]

events.description: Final stage of the Mexican War of Independence from Spain with Plan of Iguala.
events.html: • 1821 – Final stage of the Mexican War of Independence from Spain with Plan of Iguala.

events.description: The first Swaminarayan temple in the world, Shri Swaminarayan Mandir, Ahmedabad, is inaugurated.
events.html: • 1822 – The first Swaminarayan temple in the world, Shri Swaminarayan Mandir, Ahmedabad, is inaugurated.

events.description: The signing of the Treaty of Yandabo marks the end of the First Anglo-Burmese War.
events.html: • 1826 – The signing of the Treaty of Yandabo marks the end of the First Anglo-Burmese War.

events.description: The Treaty of Dancing Rabbit Creek, the first removal treaty in accordance with the Indian Removal Act, is proclaimed. The Choctaws in Mississippi cede land east of the river in exchange for payment and land in the West.
events.html: • 1831 – The Treaty of Dancing Rabbit Creek, the first removal treaty in accordance with the Indian Removal Act, is proclaimed.[17] The Choctaws in Mississippi cede land east of the river in exchange for payment and land in the West.

events.description: King Louis-Philippe of France abdicates the throne.
events.html: • 1848 – King Louis-Philippe of France abdicates the throne.[18]

events.description: A Penny Red with perforations becomes the first perforated postage stamp to be officially issued for distribution.
events.html: • 1854 – A Penny Red with perforations becomes the first perforated postage stamp to be officially issued for distribution.[19]

events.description: Arizona is organized as a United States territory.
events.html: • 1863 – Arizona is organized as a United States territory.

events.description: Andrew Johnson becomes the first President of the United States to be impeached by the United States House of Representatives. He is later acquitted in the Senate.
events.html: • 1868 – Andrew Johnson becomes the first President of the United States to be impeached by the United States House of Representatives. He is later acquitted in the Senate.[20]

events.description: The SS Gothenburg hits the Great Barrier Reef and sinks off the Australian east coast, killing approximately 100, including a number of high-profile civil servants and dignitaries.
events.html: • 1875 – The SS Gothenburg hits the Great Barrier Reef and sinks off the Australian east coast, killing approximately 100, including a number of high-profile civil servants and dignitaries.[21]

events.description: The stage première of Peer Gynt, a play by Henrik Ibsen with incidental music by Edvard Grieg, takes place in Christiania (Oslo), Norway.
events.html: • 1876 – The stage première of Peer Gynt, a play by Henrik Ibsen with incidental music by Edvard Grieg, takes place in Christiania (Oslo), Norway.[22]

events.description: China and Russia sign the Sino-Russian Ili Treaty.
events.html: • 1881 – China and Russia sign the Sino-Russian Ili Treaty.

events.description: Revolution breaks out in Baire, a town near Santiago de Cuba, beginning the Cuban War of Independence; the war ends along with the Spanish–American War in 1898.
events.html: • 1895 – Revolution breaks out in Baire, a town near Santiago de Cuba, beginning the Cuban War of Independence; the war ends along with the Spanish–American War in 1898.[23]

events.description: The Governor-General of Korea establishes a clinic called Jahyewon in Sorokdo to segregate Hansen's disease patients.
events.html: • 1916 – The Governor-General of Korea establishes a clinic called Jahyewon in Sorokdo to segregate Hansen's disease patients.

events.description: World War I: The U.S. ambassador Walter Hines Page to the United Kingdom is given the Zimmermann Telegram, in which Germany pledges to ensure the return of New Mexico, Texas, and Arizona to Mexico if Mexico declares war on the United States.
events.html: • 1917 – World War I: The U.S. ambassador Walter Hines Page to the United Kingdom is given the Zimmermann Telegram, in which Germany pledges to ensure the return of New Mexico, Texas, and Arizona to Mexico if Mexico declares war on the United States.

events.description: Estonian Declaration of Independence.
events.html: • 1918 – Estonian Declaration of Independence.[24]

events.description: Nancy Astor becomes the first woman to speak in the House of Commons of the United Kingdom following her election as a Member of Parliament (MP) three months earlier.
events.html: • 1920 – Nancy Astor becomes the first woman to speak in the House of Commons of the United Kingdom following her election as a Member of Parliament (MP) three months earlier.

entities.name: House of Commons of the United Kingdom

events.description: The Nazi Party (NSDAP) was founded by Adolf Hitler in the Hofbräuhaus beer hall in Munich, Germany
events.html: • 1920 – The Nazi Party (NSDAP) was founded by Adolf Hitler in the Hofbräuhaus beer hall in Munich, Germany

events.description: Seven hundred ninety-one Romanian Jewish refugees and crew members are killed after the MV Struma is torpedoed by the Soviet Navy.
events.html: • 1942 – Seven hundred ninety-one[25] Romanian Jewish refugees and crew members are killed after the MV Struma is torpedoed by the Soviet Navy.[26][27]

events.description: The Battle of Los Angeles: A false alarm led to an anti-aircraft barrage that lasted into the early hours of February 25.
events.html: • 1942 – The Battle of Los Angeles: A false alarm led to an anti-aircraft barrage that lasted into the early hours of February 25.

events.description: World War II: First large-scale protest march resulting in clashes with the Axis occupation forces and collaborationist police in Athens against rumours of forced mobilization of Greek workers for work in Germany.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: First large-scale protest march resulting in clashes with the Axis occupation forces and collaborationist police in Athens against rumours of forced mobilization of Greek workers for work in Germany.[28]

events.description: Egyptian Premier Ahmad Mahir Pasha is killed in Parliament after reading a decree.
events.html: • 1945 – Egyptian Premier Ahmad Mahir Pasha is killed in Parliament after reading a decree.

events.description: Colonel Juan Perón, founder of the political movement that became known as Peronism, is elected to his first term as President of Argentina.
events.html: • 1946 – Colonel Juan Perón, founder of the political movement that became known as Peronism, is elected to his first term as President of Argentina.

events.description: The Armistice Agreements are signed, to formally end the hostilities of the 1948 Arab-Israeli War.
events.html: • 1949 – The Armistice Agreements are signed, to formally end the hostilities of the 1948 Arab-Israeli War.[29]

events.description: Ghanaian coup d'état by National Liberation Council overthrows Kwame Nkrumah's Government
events.html: • 1966 – Ghanaian coup d'état by National Liberation Council overthrows Kwame Nkrumah's Government[30][31]

events.description: Cultural Revolution: Zhang Chunqiao announces the dissolution of the Shanghai People's Commune, replacing its local government with a revolutionary committee.
events.html: • 1967 – Cultural Revolution: Zhang Chunqiao announces the dissolution of the Shanghai People's Commune, replacing its local government with a revolutionary committee.[32]

events.description: Vietnam War: The Tet Offensive is halted; South Vietnamese forces led by Ngo Quang Truong recapture the citadel of Hué.
events.html: • 1968 – Vietnam War: The Tet Offensive is halted; South Vietnamese forces led by Ngo Quang Truong recapture the citadel of Hué.[33]

events.description: The All India Forward Bloc holds an emergency central committee meeting after its chairman, Hemantha Kumar Bose, is killed three days earlier. P.K. Mookiah Thevar is appointed as the new chairman.
events.html: • 1971 – The All India Forward Bloc holds an emergency central committee meeting after its chairman, Hemantha Kumar Bose, is killed three days earlier. P.K. Mookiah Thevar is appointed as the new chairman.

events.description: The 1976 constitution of Cuba is formally proclaimed.
events.html: • 1976 – The 1976 constitution of Cuba is formally proclaimed.

events.description: The Yuba County Five disappear in California. Four of their bodies are found four months later.
events.html: • 1978 – The Yuba County Five disappear in California. Four of their bodies are found four months later.

events.description: The 6.7 .mw-parser-output .tooltip-dotted{border-bottom:1px dotted;cursor:help}Ms Gulf of Corinth earthquake affected Central Greece with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe). Twenty-two people were killed, 400 were injured, and damage totaled $812 million.
events.html: • 1981 – The 6.7 Ms Gulf of Corinth earthquake affected Central Greece with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe). Twenty-two people were killed, 400 were injured, and damage totaled $812 million.

events.description: A special commission of the United States Congress condemns the Japanese American internment during World War II.
events.html: • 1983 – A special commission of the United States Congress condemns the Japanese American internment during World War II.

events.description: Tyrone Mitchell perpetrates the 49th Street Elementary School shooting in Los Angeles, killing two children and injuring 12 more.
events.html: • 1984 – Tyrone Mitchell perpetrates the 49th Street Elementary School shooting in Los Angeles, killing two children and injuring 12 more.

events.description: United Airlines Flight 811, bound for New Zealand from Honolulu, rips open during flight, blowing nine passengers out of the business-class section.
events.html: • 1989 – United Airlines Flight 811, bound for New Zealand from Honolulu, rips open during flight, blowing nine passengers out of the business-class section.

events.description: Gulf War: Ground troops cross the Saudi Arabian border and enter Iraq, thus beginning the ground phase of the war.
events.html: • 1991 – Gulf War: Ground troops cross the Saudi Arabian border and enter Iraq, thus beginning the ground phase of the war.

events.description: Two civilian airplanes operated by the Miami-based group Brothers to the Rescue are shot down in international waters by the Cuban Air Force.
events.html: • 1996 – Two civilian airplanes operated by the Miami-based group Brothers to the Rescue are shot down in international waters by the Cuban Air Force.

entities.name: 1996 shootdown of Brothers to the Rescue aircraft

events.description: China Southwest Airlines Flight 4509, a Tupolev Tu-154 aircraft, crashes in Rui'an, Zhejiang, China. All 61 people on board are killed.
events.html: • 1999 – China Southwest Airlines Flight 4509, a Tupolev Tu-154 aircraft, crashes in Rui'an, Zhejiang, China. All 61 people on board are killed.[34]

events.description: The 6.3 Mw Al Hoceima earthquake strikes northern Morocco with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent). At least 628 people are killed, 926 are injured, and up to 15,000 are displaced.
events.html: • 2004 – The 6.3 Mw Al Hoceima earthquake strikes northern Morocco with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent). At least 628 people are killed, 926 are injured, and up to 15,000 are displaced.

events.description: Philippine President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo declares Proclamation 1017 placing the country in a state of emergency in attempt to subdue a possible military coup.
events.html: • 2006 – Philippine President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo declares Proclamation 1017 placing the country in a state of emergency in attempt to subdue a possible military coup.

entities.name: 2006 state of emergency in the Philippines

events.description: Japan launches its fourth spy satellite, stepping up its ability to monitor potential threats such as North Korea.
events.html: • 2007 – Japan launches its fourth spy satellite, stepping up its ability to monitor potential threats such as North Korea.

events.description: Fidel Castro retires as the President of Cuba and the Council of Ministers after 32 years. He remains as head of the Communist Party for another three years.
events.html: • 2008 – Fidel Castro retires as the President of Cuba and the Council of Ministers after 32 years. He remains as head of the Communist Party for another three years.

events.description: A Metrolink train derails in Oxnard, California following a collision with a truck, leaving more than 30 injured.
events.html: • 2015 – A Metrolink train derails in Oxnard, California following a collision with a truck, leaving more than 30 injured.

events.description: Tara Air Flight 193, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter aircraft, crashed, with 23 fatalities, in Solighopte, Myagdi District, Dhaulagiri Zone, while en route from Pokhara Airport to Jomsom Airport.
events.html: • 2016 – Tara Air Flight 193, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter aircraft, crashed, with 23 fatalities, in Solighopte, Myagdi District, Dhaulagiri Zone, while en route from Pokhara Airport to Jomsom Airport.

entities.name: De Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter

events.description: Mahathir Mohamad resigns as Prime Minister of Malaysia following an attempt to replace the Pakatan Harapan government, which triggered the 2020-2022 Malaysian political crisis.
events.html: • 2020 – Mahathir Mohamad resigns as Prime Minister of Malaysia following an attempt to replace the Pakatan Harapan government, which triggered the 2020-2022 Malaysian political crisis.[35]

events.description: Russo-Ukrainian War: Days after recognising Donetsk and Luhansk as independent states, Russian president Vladimir Putin orders a full-scale invasion of Ukraine.
events.html: • 2022 – Russo-Ukrainian War: Days after recognising Donetsk and Luhansk as independent states, Russian president Vladimir Putin orders a full-scale invasion of Ukraine.[36]
